{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KxSmpApK5xnCTuSmWZ7Zh8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and compiled detailed findings on all requested areas. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. WEB PORTAL - Files & Architecture\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Core Handler:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,214 lines) - Main HTTP handler with embedded templates and static assets\n\n**HTML Templates** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`):\n- `layout.html` - Base template with navbar and layout structure\n- `projects.html` - Project overview page with project cards and health indicators\n- `runs.html` - All runs list view with project filtering and status badges\n- `run_detail.html` - Run detail view with step timeline, container status, and live log streaming\n- `project_detail.html` - Project detail page with info panel, workflows DAG, and prompt file history\n\n**Styling:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (12,616 bytes) - Complete CSS with dark mode support\n\n**Web Handler Routes:**\n```\nGET /              → handleProjectOverview (project cards)\nGET /projects/{name} → handleProjectDetail (project info)\nGET /projects/{name}/runs → redirect to /runs?project={dir}\nGET /runs          → handleRunsList (all runs table)\nGET /runs/{id}     → handleRunDetail (run details)\nGET /static/*      → Static file server\nGET /api/projects  → JSON API: list all projects with health\nGET /api/runs      → JSON API: list runs (filterable by project)\nGET /api/runs/{id} → JSON API: run detail with container state and steps\nGET /api/runs/{id}/stream → SSE: live log streaming\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output → Get step output/logs\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container → Delete a retained container\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info → Docker image, version, prompt history\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff → Git diff for prompt files\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows → Parse and return all workflows as JSON DAG\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content → Step content\n```\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Embedded FS:** Templates and static files are embedded using `//go:embed`\n- **Template Functions:** `stateColor`, `healthColor`, `formatTime`, `formatDuration`, `truncate`, `shortContainerID`\n- **Live Features:**\n  - SSE (Server-Sent Events) for real-time log streaming\n  - 2-3 second polling for active run details\n  - Accordion UI for step output expansion\n  - Container state inspection and deletion\n\n---\n\n### 2. DAEMON API - gRPC Service Definitions\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (98 lines)\n\n**gRPC Service Endpoints:**\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) → RunWorkflowResponse\n  rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) → GetStatusResponse\n  rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) → stream LogEntry\n  rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) → StopRunResponse\n  rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) → ListRunsResponse\n  rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) → ShutdownResponse\n  rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) → DeleteContainerResponse\n}\n```\n\n**Key Messages:**\n\n`RunWorkflowRequest`:\n- workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container\n\n`GetStatusResponse`:\n- run_id, workflow_name, state, current_step, step_executions[], error_message\n- container_id, container_alive, container_dead_since\n\n`StepExecutionStatus`:\n- step_name, result, started_at, completed_at\n\n`StreamLogsRequest`:\n- run_id, step_name, log_type (optional filter)\n\n`LogEntry`:\n- type, step_name, result, message, timestamp\n\n`ListRunsResponse`:\n- runs[] (RunSummary) with id, workflow_name, state, started_at, error_message, container_id\n\n**gRPC Server Implementation:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (700+ lines)\n- Launches containers in background goroutines\n- Tracks run state through JSON-line protocol messages from agents\n- Manages container lifecycle (start → track → extract outputs → cleanup)\n- Indexes log files in SQLite\n- Fires evolution triggers on completion\n\n---\n\n### 3. HOW RUNS ARE DISPLAYED IN WEB PORTAL\n\n**Run Detail View** (`run_detail.html`):\n- **Header Section:**\n  - Run ID, workflow name, status badge\n  - Started/completed times, container ID\n  - Container status indicator (running/stopped/available/removed)\n  - Container delete button (visible for completed runs with kept containers)\n\n- **Steps Table:**\n  - Lists step name, result (success/fail/running), started time, duration\n  - Expandable accordion rows for step output/logs\n  - Output lazily fetched on click via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n- **Log Viewer:**\n  - Real-time SSE stream from `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n  - Displays entries as `[timestamp] [type] content`\n  - Log types: \"script\", \"llm\" (Claude streaming output parsed)\n  - Auto-scroll tracking, manual scroll disables auto-scroll\n  - For completed runs: serves archived `full.log` from disk\n\n**Step Output Retrieval:**\n- First tries log index (SQLite log_files table)\n- Falls back to file path: `.cloche/{runID}/output/{step}.log`\n- If not found, tries `container.log`\n- Last resort: live Docker logs from container if still exists\n\n**Container State Detection:**\n```go\ncontainerState():\n  \"running\"   → container exists, is running\n  \"stopped\"   → container exists, not running, not kept\n  \"available\" → container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n  \"removed\"   → no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CONTAINER LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT - Docker Adapter\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/` (8,352 bytes)\n\n**Docker Runtime Methods:**\n\n`Start(cfg ContainerConfig) → containerID, error`:\n- Creates container via `docker create`\n- Copies project files into `/workspace/` (no bind mount)\n- Applies `.cloche/overrides/` files on top\n- Copies Claude auth files to container\n- Supports extra mounts via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`\n- Supports extra env vars via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n- Wraps default command: chown workspace → strip unneeded tools → exec as agent user\n- Returns container ID\n\n`Stop(containerID) → error`:\n- Runs `docker stop`\n\n`AttachOutput(containerID) → io.ReadCloser, error`:\n- Returns `docker logs -f` stream for reading agent output\n\n`Wait(containerID) → exitCode, error`:\n- Runs `docker wait` and parses exit code\n\n`CopyFrom(containerID, srcPath, dstPath) → error`:\n- Runs `docker cp` to extract files from container to host\n\n`Logs(containerID) → string, error`:\n- Returns full container stdout + stderr combined\n\n`Remove(containerID) → error`:\n- Runs `docker rm` to delete container\n\n`Inspect(containerID) → ContainerStatus, error`:\n- Uses `docker inspect` with format template\n- Returns `ContainerStatus` with Running bool, ExitCode, FinishedAt\n\n**Container Lifecycle in gRPC Server:**\n1. `RunWorkflow` RPC triggers `launchAndTrack()` in background goroutine\n2. Ensures image exists (if `ImageEnsurer` available)\n3. `Start()` container with project files\n4. Records in store: `run.Start()`, `run.ContainerID = containerID`\n5. `AttachOutput()` and parse JSON-line status messages\n6. On each message: `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, save to captures store\n7. Wait for container exit\n8. Extract outputs to `.cloche/{runID}/output/` directory\n9. Extract results to git branch (`cloche/{runID}` branch)\n10. Finalize run state (succeeded/failed)\n11. **Retention Policy:**\n    - Failed runs: always keep container\n    - Successful with `--keep-container` flag: keep container\n    - Successful without flag: `Remove()` container\n    - Mark `run.ContainerKept = true` in store if kept\n\n---\n\n### 5. RUN STATUS/STATE TYPES\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (110 lines)\n\n**RunState Constants:**\n```go\nconst (\n  RunStatePending   = \"pending\"   // Before container starts\n  RunStateRunning   = \"running\"   // Container is executing\n  RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\" // Completed successfully\n  RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"    // Exited with error\n  RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\" // Manually stopped\n)\n```\n\n**Run Struct:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string          // Unique run ID (generated from workflow name)\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState\n  ActiveSteps    []string        // Currently executing steps\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution // History of all step executions\n  StartedAt      time.Time\n  CompletedAt    time.Time\n  ProjectDir     string          // Full path to project directory\n  ErrorMessage   string\n  ContainerID    string          // Docker container ID\n  BaseSHA        string          // Git HEAD at run start (for branch creation)\n  ContainerKept  bool            // Whether container was retained\n}\n```\n\n**StepExecution Struct:**\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n  StepName    string\n  Result      string          // \"success\", \"fail\", or empty (running)\n  StartedAt   time.Time\n  CompletedAt time.Time\n  Logs        string\n  GitRef      string          // Output state (git branch)\n}\n```\n\n**Run Methods:**\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName)` → initializes with state=pending\n- `Start()` → sets state=running, StartedAt=now\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` → adds to ActiveSteps, creates StepExecution with StartedAt\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` → removes from ActiveSteps, updates StepExecution with result and CompletedAt\n- `Complete(state)` → sets final state (succeeded/cancelled), sets CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)` → sets state=failed, CompletedAt, ErrorMessage\n\n**HealthResult (Project Health):**\n```go\ntype HealthResult struct {\n  Status HealthStatus  // green, yellow, red, blue, grey\n  Passed int\n  Failed int\n  Total  int\n}\n\n// Rules:\n// Grey  → no runs\n// Blue  → all active (pending/running)\n// Green → all completed succeeded\n// Red   → all completed failed/cancelled\n// Yellow → mix of passed and failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. STORAGE LAYER - SQLite Adapter\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (15,338 bytes)\n\n**Database Schema:**\n\n`runs` table:\n```sql\nid, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at,\nproject_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept\n```\n\n`step_executions` table:\n```sql\nid, run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at,\nlogs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n```\n\n`log_files` table:\n```sql\nid, run_id, step_name, file_type (full/script/llm), file_path, file_size, created_at\n```\n\n`evolution_log` table (for self-evolution tracking)\n\n**Store Interfaces:**\n\n`RunStore`:\n- CreateRun, GetRun, UpdateRun, DeleteRun\n- ListRuns(since time.Time), ListRunsByProject(projectDir, since)\n- ListProjects()\n\n`CaptureStore`:\n- SaveCapture(runID, StepExecution)\n- GetCaptures(runID) → []*StepExecution\n\n`LogStore`:\n- SaveLogFile(LogFileEntry)\n- GetLogFiles(runID)\n- GetLogFilesByStep(runID, stepName)\n- GetLogFileByType(runID, fileType)\n\n---\n\n### 7. DAEMON STARTUP - Web Server Integration\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (246 lines)\n\n**Web Server Setup:**\n```go\nif httpAddr != \"\" {\n  webOpts := []web.HandlerOption{\n    web.WithContainerLogger(runtime),\n    web.WithLogStore(store),\n    web.WithLogBroadcaster(broadcaster),\n  }\n  webHandler, err := web.NewHandler(store, store, webOpts...)\n  httpServer := &http.Server{Addr: httpAddr, Handler: webHandler}\n  go httpServer.ListenAndServe()\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration Sources:**\n- Environment variables: `CLOCHE_HTTP`, `CLOCHE_LISTEN`, `CLOCHE_DB`, `CLOCHE_IMAGE`, `CLOCHE_RUNTIME`\n- Global config: `~/.config/cloche/config`\n- Fallback defaults\n\n**Key Features:**\n- gRPC server on unix socket or TCP (CLOCHE_LISTEN)\n- HTTP web portal on TCP (CLOCHE_HTTP, optional)\n- Both servers run concurrently in same process\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n---\n\n### Summary File Locations\n\n**Web Portal:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (main router and API endpoints)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/{layout,projects,runs,run_detail,project_detail}.html`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n**gRPC API:**\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (service definitions)\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/` (generated Go protobuf code)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (implementation)\n\n**Container Management:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (Docker operations)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` (Image building)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` (Result extraction)\n\n**Data Models:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (Run and RunState)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go` (Health indicators)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (Workflow and Step definitions)\n\n**Storage:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (Database implementation)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (Store interfaces)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` (Container runtime interfaces)\n\n**Daemon:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (Daemon entrypoint with web/gRPC servers)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1d08d7694be0cb94 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75710\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 74597</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2566a3c-e8d8-43a6-bf93-08a9f5a6e841","uuid":"9257d714-050b-4084-b79a-772465e4b64e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand:\n1. The web portal - find all files related to it (HTML templates, handlers, routes)\n2. The daemon API - gRPC service definitions, especially any existing container management endpoints\n3. How runs are displayed in the web portal (log/run-details view)\n4. How container lifecycle is managed (Docker adapter)\n5. The run status/state types\n\nFocus on:\n- Finding the web portal handler files and templates\n- Finding gRPC proto files\n- Finding container-related code in adapters\n- Finding run state/status types\n\nBe very thorough - check cmd/cloched/ for web server setup, internal/adapters/ for implementations, and any proto files.","agentId":"a1d08d7694be0cb94","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and compiled detailed findings on all requested areas. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. WEB PORTAL - Files & Architecture\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Core Handler:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,214 lines) - Main HTTP handler with embedded templates and static assets\n\n**HTML Templates** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`):\n- `layout.html` - Base template with navbar and layout structure\n- `projects.html` - Project overview page with project cards and health indicators\n- `runs.html` - All runs list view with project filtering and status badges\n- `run_detail.html` - Run detail view with step timeline, container status, and live log streaming\n- `project_detail.html` - Project detail page with info panel, workflows DAG, and prompt file history\n\n**Styling:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (12,616 bytes) - Complete CSS with dark mode support\n\n**Web Handler Routes:**\n```\nGET /              → handleProjectOverview (project cards)\nGET /projects/{name} → handleProjectDetail (project info)\nGET /projects/{name}/runs → redirect to /runs?project={dir}\nGET /runs          → handleRunsList (all runs table)\nGET /runs/{id}     → handleRunDetail (run details)\nGET /static/*      → Static file server\nGET /api/projects  → JSON API: list all projects with health\nGET /api/runs      → JSON API: list runs (filterable by project)\nGET /api/runs/{id} → JSON API: run detail with container state and steps\nGET /api/runs/{id}/stream → SSE: live log streaming\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output → Get step output/logs\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container → Delete a retained container\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info → Docker image, version, prompt history\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff → Git diff for prompt files\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows → Parse and return all workflows as JSON DAG\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content → Step content\n```\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Embedded FS:** Templates and static files are embedded using `//go:embed`\n- **Template Functions:** `stateColor`, `healthColor`, `formatTime`, `formatDuration`, `truncate`, `shortContainerID`\n- **Live Features:**\n  - SSE (Server-Sent Events) for real-time log streaming\n  - 2-3 second polling for active run details\n  - Accordion UI for step output expansion\n  - Container state inspection and deletion\n\n---\n\n### 2. DAEMON API - gRPC Service Definitions\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (98 lines)\n\n**gRPC Service Endpoints:**\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) → RunWorkflowResponse\n  rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) → GetStatusResponse\n  rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) → stream LogEntry\n  rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) → StopRunResponse\n  rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) → ListRunsResponse\n  rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) → ShutdownResponse\n  rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) → DeleteContainerResponse\n}\n```\n\n**Key Messages:**\n\n`RunWorkflowRequest`:\n- workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container\n\n`GetStatusResponse`:\n- run_id, workflow_name, state, current_step, step_executions[], error_message\n- container_id, container_alive, container_dead_since\n\n`StepExecutionStatus`:\n- step_name, result, started_at, completed_at\n\n`StreamLogsRequest`:\n- run_id, step_name, log_type (optional filter)\n\n`LogEntry`:\n- type, step_name, result, message, timestamp\n\n`ListRunsResponse`:\n- runs[] (RunSummary) with id, workflow_name, state, started_at, error_message, container_id\n\n**gRPC Server Implementation:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (700+ lines)\n- Launches containers in background goroutines\n- Tracks run state through JSON-line protocol messages from agents\n- Manages container lifecycle (start → track → extract outputs → cleanup)\n- Indexes log files in SQLite\n- Fires evolution triggers on completion\n\n---\n\n### 3. HOW RUNS ARE DISPLAYED IN WEB PORTAL\n\n**Run Detail View** (`run_detail.html`):\n- **Header Section:**\n  - Run ID, workflow name, status badge\n  - Started/completed times, container ID\n  - Container status indicator (running/stopped/available/removed)\n  - Container delete button (visible for completed runs with kept containers)\n\n- **Steps Table:**\n  - Lists step name, result (success/fail/running), started time, duration\n  - Expandable accordion rows for step output/logs\n  - Output lazily fetched on click via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n- **Log Viewer:**\n  - Real-time SSE stream from `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n  - Displays entries as `[timestamp] [type] content`\n  - Log types: \"script\", \"llm\" (Claude streaming output parsed)\n  - Auto-scroll tracking, manual scroll disables auto-scroll\n  - For completed runs: serves archived `full.log` from disk\n\n**Step Output Retrieval:**\n- First tries log index (SQLite log_files table)\n- Falls back to file path: `.cloche/{runID}/output/{step}.log`\n- If not found, tries `container.log`\n- Last resort: live Docker logs from container if still exists\n\n**Container State Detection:**\n```go\ncontainerState():\n  \"running\"   → container exists, is running\n  \"stopped\"   → container exists, not running, not kept\n  \"available\" → container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n  \"removed\"   → no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CONTAINER LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT - Docker Adapter\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/` (8,352 bytes)\n\n**Docker Runtime Methods:**\n\n`Start(cfg ContainerConfig) → containerID, error`:\n- Creates container via `docker create`\n- Copies project files into `/workspace/` (no bind mount)\n- Applies `.cloche/overrides/` files on top\n- Copies Claude auth files to container\n- Supports extra mounts via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`\n- Supports extra env vars via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n- Wraps default command: chown workspace → strip unneeded tools → exec as agent user\n- Returns container ID\n\n`Stop(containerID) → error`:\n- Runs `docker stop`\n\n`AttachOutput(containerID) → io.ReadCloser, error`:\n- Returns `docker logs -f` stream for reading agent output\n\n`Wait(containerID) → exitCode, error`:\n- Runs `docker wait` and parses exit code\n\n`CopyFrom(containerID, srcPath, dstPath) → error`:\n- Runs `docker cp` to extract files from container to host\n\n`Logs(containerID) → string, error`:\n- Returns full container stdout + stderr combined\n\n`Remove(containerID) → error`:\n- Runs `docker rm` to delete container\n\n`Inspect(containerID) → ContainerStatus, error`:\n- Uses `docker inspect` with format template\n- Returns `ContainerStatus` with Running bool, ExitCode, FinishedAt\n\n**Container Lifecycle in gRPC Server:**\n1. `RunWorkflow` RPC triggers `launchAndTrack()` in background goroutine\n2. Ensures image exists (if `ImageEnsurer` available)\n3. `Start()` container with project files\n4. Records in store: `run.Start()`, `run.ContainerID = containerID`\n5. `AttachOutput()` and parse JSON-line status messages\n6. On each message: `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, save to captures store\n7. Wait for container exit\n8. Extract outputs to `.cloche/{runID}/output/` directory\n9. Extract results to git branch (`cloche/{runID}` branch)\n10. Finalize run state (succeeded/failed)\n11. **Retention Policy:**\n    - Failed runs: always keep container\n    - Successful with `--keep-container` flag: keep container\n    - Successful without flag: `Remove()` container\n    - Mark `run.ContainerKept = true` in store if kept\n\n---\n\n### 5. RUN STATUS/STATE TYPES\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (110 lines)\n\n**RunState Constants:**\n```go\nconst (\n  RunStatePending   = \"pending\"   // Before container starts\n  RunStateRunning   = \"running\"   // Container is executing\n  RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\" // Completed successfully\n  RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"    // Exited with error\n  RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\" // Manually stopped\n)\n```\n\n**Run Struct:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string          // Unique run ID (generated from workflow name)\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState\n  ActiveSteps    []string        // Currently executing steps\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution // History of all step executions\n  StartedAt      time.Time\n  CompletedAt    time.Time\n  ProjectDir     string          // Full path to project directory\n  ErrorMessage   string\n  ContainerID    string          // Docker container ID\n  BaseSHA        string          // Git HEAD at run start (for branch creation)\n  ContainerKept  bool            // Whether container was retained\n}\n```\n\n**StepExecution Struct:**\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n  StepName    string\n  Result      string          // \"success\", \"fail\", or empty (running)\n  StartedAt   time.Time\n  CompletedAt time.Time\n  Logs        string\n  GitRef      string          // Output state (git branch)\n}\n```\n\n**Run Methods:**\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName)` → initializes with state=pending\n- `Start()` → sets state=running, StartedAt=now\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` → adds to ActiveSteps, creates StepExecution with StartedAt\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` → removes from ActiveSteps, updates StepExecution with result and CompletedAt\n- `Complete(state)` → sets final state (succeeded/cancelled), sets CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)` → sets state=failed, CompletedAt, ErrorMessage\n\n**HealthResult (Project Health):**\n```go\ntype HealthResult struct {\n  Status HealthStatus  // green, yellow, red, blue, grey\n  Passed int\n  Failed int\n  Total  int\n}\n\n// Rules:\n// Grey  → no runs\n// Blue  → all active (pending/running)\n// Green → all completed succeeded\n// Red   → all completed failed/cancelled\n// Yellow → mix of passed and failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. STORAGE LAYER - SQLite Adapter\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (15,338 bytes)\n\n**Database Schema:**\n\n`runs` table:\n```sql\nid, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at,\nproject_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept\n```\n\n`step_executions` table:\n```sql\nid, run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at,\nlogs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n```\n\n`log_files` table:\n```sql\nid, run_id, step_name, file_type (full/script/llm), file_path, file_size, created_at\n```\n\n`evolution_log` table (for self-evolution tracking)\n\n**Store Interfaces:**\n\n`RunStore`:\n- CreateRun, GetRun, UpdateRun, DeleteRun\n- ListRuns(since time.Time), ListRunsByProject(projectDir, since)\n- ListProjects()\n\n`CaptureStore`:\n- SaveCapture(runID, StepExecution)\n- GetCaptures(runID) → []*StepExecution\n\n`LogStore`:\n- SaveLogFile(LogFileEntry)\n- GetLogFiles(runID)\n- GetLogFilesByStep(runID, stepName)\n- GetLogFileByType(runID, fileType)\n\n---\n\n### 7. DAEMON STARTUP - Web Server Integration\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (246 lines)\n\n**Web Server Setup:**\n```go\nif httpAddr != \"\" {\n  webOpts := []web.HandlerOption{\n    web.WithContainerLogger(runtime),\n    web.WithLogStore(store),\n    web.WithLogBroadcaster(broadcaster),\n  }\n  webHandler, err := web.NewHandler(store, store, webOpts...)\n  httpServer := &http.Server{Addr: httpAddr, Handler: webHandler}\n  go httpServer.ListenAndServe()\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration Sources:**\n- Environment variables: `CLOCHE_HTTP`, `CLOCHE_LISTEN`, `CLOCHE_DB`, `CLOCHE_IMAGE`, `CLOCHE_RUNTIME`\n- Global config: `~/.config/cloche/config`\n- Fallback defaults\n\n**Key Features:**\n- gRPC server on unix socket or TCP (CLOCHE_LISTEN)\n- HTTP web portal on TCP (CLOCHE_HTTP, optional)\n- Both servers run concurrently in same process\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n---\n\n### Summary File Locations\n\n**Web Portal:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (main router and API endpoints)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/{layout,projects,runs,run_detail,project_detail}.html`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n**gRPC API:**\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (service definitions)\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/` (generated Go protobuf code)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (implementation)\n\n**Container Management:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (Docker operations)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` (Image building)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` (Result extraction)\n\n**Data Models:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (Run and RunState)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go` (Health indicators)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (Workflow and Step definitions)\n\n**Storage:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (Database implementation)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (Store interfaces)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` (Container runtime interfaces)\n\n**Daemon:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (Daemon entrypoint with web/gRPC servers)"}],"totalDurationM